Pandemonium broke out in the early hours on Thursday, at Obalende area of Lagos Island following violent clash betweens rival groups of National Union of Road Transport Workers, NURTW. According to sources, people were seen running in different directions for safety while several properties were said to have been destroyed. Scores of people were also said several people sustained injuries. The clash, which is still ongoing, it was gathered started at about 8 am. At press time, it could not be ascertained if there were causalities as well as the cause of the clash. Meantime, residents and motorists have been urged to avoid the area for now pending the arrival of security personnel to restore sanity and safety. Vanguard News Nigeria DAYS after two rival factions of the National Union of Road Transport Workers, NURTW, engaged themselves in a bloody clash at the Ijebu-Ode motor park, many residents of Ijebu-Ode in Ogun State, are still counting their losses, especially families who lost dear ones or had their property destroyed in theâ€¦ November 25, 2011 In "Metro" SOME states in the South-West geo-political zone, especially Lagos, Osun and Ondo states, are grappling with the activities of cultists. The menace is gradually spreading like wildfire across these states. January 7, 2021 In "News" Pandemonium broke out at the early hours of Wednesday at Oshodi in Lagos State when two rival thugs group clashed, leaving no fewer than two yet-to-be identified persons dead. February 25, 2015 In "News"